                    h2.mb-5 Projects

                    d-flex.flex-column.flex-md-row.justify-content-between.mb-5
                        .flex-grow-1
                            h3.mb-0 Game Hosting Service
                            .fs-6.fw-normal.mb-4 Web service to manage hosting services specially games

                            .subheading.mb-3 
                                a(href='https://github.com/josh-mchugh/game-hosting') Web Application
                            p
                                | Spring Boot application which allows for users to create accounts and spin up virtual machines. Was an experimential project to test code architecture designs and practice test driven development. It uses Axon for CRQS and it's event logs. It also uses AWX to execute Ansible scripts on the newly created servers.

                    d-flex.flex-column.flex-md-row.justify-content-between.mb-5
                        .flex-grow-1
                            h3.mb-0 TubeCentric
                            .fs-6.fw-normal.mb-4 Software to help YouTube Creators improve video meta data

                            .subheading.mb-3 
                                a(href='https://github.com/josh-mchugh/tubecentric') Web Application
                            p
                                | Spring Boot application to handle Restful API calls to the Browser Extension as well as serve a landing page for a domain to drive users to install the browser extension. It was deployed on Digital Ocean and used Docker, Kubernetes, and Helm for it's continous deployment.
                            
                            .subheading.mb-3 
                                a(href='https://github.com/josh-mchugh/tube-centric-browser-extension-3') Chrome Extension 
                            p
                                | Browser extension for both Chrome and Firefox. It worked with the TubeCentric Web application to provide ranked results to users who have it installed. When the user was on the correct page, the browser extentsion would inject ReactJS scripts into the page to allow the user to interact with the TubeCentric web application.

                            .subheading.mb-3 
                                a(href='https://github.com/josh-mchugh/waldo') Waldo
                            p  
                                | Spring Boot application which used the Twitter API to listen to new tweets stream for related topics. Related topics were liked, to encourage user enagement with a Twitter account. The assumption was I would be able to direct traffic to the TubeCentric landing page in a passive manner to encourage the browser extension download.

                    d-flex.flex-column.flex-md-row.justify-content-between.mb-5
